A 27-year-old Austin woman who was charged with causing a fatal DUI accident that killed her friend was sentenced to 10 days in jail after the victim’s parents asked the judge for leniency.

Police said Madeline Rackley, then 25 years old, drove her car into Lady Bird Lake in July 2012 after spending the night drinking with friends in an Austin bar.

Rackley and a female front-seat passenger were able to escape from the sinking car, but 25-year-old Jarrett Ryan Whittington, who was in the backseat, was unable to free himself and drowned.

